60 Troll Warrior Baron<BR>
Veil of Shadows</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utaranaro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TaranaRo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.telocity.com/~tarana1/daku_mini.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 102<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/27/02 11:14:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1312.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cazic Thule - tell me again why I should bother?</span><hr size=1> Faed with that group you could do very well in Pools (very fast kills for CT, only 1 caster and he is a rare) but you will have to learn to pull from the green pool without getting adds. The hall can be pulled two at a time max if you take time to observe the pathing of the 2 or 3 roamers there.<br>
<br>
Also is sewers. This requires more DPS and better CC as the skeeters and pools can get nasty but still very manageable. Again a camp with 0 casters.<br>
<br>
Next I'd say is maze, very few casters if your puller knows the pathing and where to look but you will have to deal with the fast dmg raptors to do so. Good place to hunt with many rares.<br>
<br>
After Maze I'd say is LTR (Lower Throne Room) it's a good xp spot but mostly casters so have those clicky earrings/legs ready to cure disease to remove slow. If you can keep from being slowed too much and have good DPS this is a nice spot.<br>
<br>
After that your group is gonna have it rough. Maybe get another group and split 4c between the two, or go for the fish ponds if you don't mind fighting in the water. Fish ponds have rares as well but noone ever hunts them on my server.<br>
<br>
Also you can try for the mud bowl area but this gets rather hard with a single group. Lots of shammy mobs so expect to be slowed alot. Really at this point you need to be the uber high dps group or a mini-raid splitting the spawns.<br>
<br>
In my opinion CT is still one of the best zones in the game for both xp and fun. And depending on which area you are in it's a fun crawl dungeon too as some of the areas remain uncamped even on high population servers like mine. <p><center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=56851><img src=http://members.telocity.com/~tarana1/sig_daku_custom.jpg border=0></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usulvar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sulvar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/27/02 2:02:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1312.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cazic Thule - tell me again why I should bother?</span><hr size=1> TaranaRo is right on about the order of camps in CT.  I would suggest working your way up from the easiest camps to the hardest camps.  If it is your first time in CT definately start at the strip of land between the pools (old blue/green gator pools).  Once you have a good handle on this you can start doing the maze, planks, and the lower TR.  All of these camps are about the same difficulty.  Lower TR might be considered a little harder because of the AoE casters that spawn there.<br>
<br>
A couple of things that I have learned about CT are that it is good to bring along some sort of FD puller and a wizard.  The AoE casters are extreme bastards, but they have low hps compared to the rest of the mobs in CT.  My CT groups usually rely on our 60th wizard to burn down the AoE caster lizards fast.<br>
<br>
As for the 4C, I camped the 4C last night and got ~40% aa xp in 2 hour.  The adept also spawned and we got another lizard bone earring for our guild shaman.  While there I didn't notice anything new about the pathing, but then again 4C pathing has always been a little odd, even in the days of old CT. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=179608>Gartuff</a>
<br><i>Halfling Warlord</i>
